    "reasoning": "Step 1: From the equations x1(x1+1)=A and x2(x2+1)=A, x1 and x2 are distinct complex numbers, so they are the two distinct roots of x^2+x-A=0. Using Vieta, x1+x2=-1 and x1x2=-A. Step 2: The third equation x1^4+3x1^3+5x1 = x2^4+3x2^3+5x2 implies P(x1)=P(x2) where P(x)=x^4+3x^3+5x. Compute P(x1)-P(x2)=0 and divide by (x1-x2) (nonzero) to get an equation in terms of symmetric sums. Substituting x1+x2=-1 and x1x2=-A yields 7+A=0, so A=-7. Step 3: Then k = A+9 = 2. Step 4: Evaluate the sum S = sum_{n=2}^{17} (n^2+n+1)/(n^4+2n^3-n^2-2n). Simplify denominator: n^4+2n^3-n^2-2n = (n-1)n(n+1)(n+2). Step 5: Perform partial fraction decomposition: (n^2+n+1)/[(n-1)n(n+1)(n+2)] = 1/(2(n-1)) - 1/(2n) + 1/(2(n+1)) - 1/(2(n+2)). Step 6: The sum telescopes: S = (1/2) sum_{n=2}^{17} [1/(n-1)-1/n+1/(n+1)-1/(n+2)] = (1/2)(1 + 1/3 - 1/17 - 1/19) = (1/2)(4/3 - 36/323) = (1/2)(1184/969) = 592/969.",
    "answer": "592/969"
